  "summary": "Malicious code in xeiko-cdn (npm)",
  "details": "Package xeiko-cdn is a fake CDN package that, when loaded in a browser, injects a remote tracking script (node12[.]aizhantj[.]com:21233) and creates a full-page iframe overlay to a date-rotating subdomain on 182[.]run. It also disables right-click context menu, text selection, and the F12 developer tools key to prevent users from inspecting the injected content. The iframe URL follows a daily-rotation pattern using the current date (DDMM[.]182[.]run). This is a supply-chain compromise distributing browser-side ad-injection / clickjack / tracking payloads via npm.",
